{
  "stem": "11274.3",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And with this family, there was-- well-to-do family, they had a housekeeper, and they had a cook, and a cleaning woman.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I was the spice assistant.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I had the keys and always went with the woman to do shopping, the shopping.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I watched the things that she was taking out there for the cooking and helping a little bit with the cooking there in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then there were rumors again they're going to take Jewish people, and especially young girls they're going to start taking.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the family-- Stahler was their name, from the family that I was, with the Jewish family-- and said would be better-- [CLEARS THROAT] --that you be in small place.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we got contacted some family.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I forgot to tell you, this spring-- that spring, [INAUDIBLE]-- this is already almost six months later, what I'm telling you now.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But before that, it was Passover, and I, I tried to call-- the first Passover when I was at my uncles, I sent over raisins that father could make the wine at home for Passover, and I send over matzos in a package.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And they received it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But this is the second Passover I'm there, and I knew a Jewish tailor that was a sewing, forcefully sewing, for the-- by force-- sewing for the officers, leather coats.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I knew him, and I said, I would like to call.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How do you go about it calling my parents and seeing if they're still there so I can send a package?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He said, well, I'm going to bribe one of the officers and tell him I give him two coats so that the other officers don't know about it-- or a coat for his wife or something.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
